                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#105rc">f. 105rc</locus>
                           <desc>: Excerpt from Dǝggʷā (Antiphonary) for Good Thursday. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in the same hand as Additio 2. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#105va">f. 105va</locus>
                           <desc>: Excerpt from Zǝmmāre (Eucharistic hymns). </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in the same hand as Additio 1. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#106r">f. 106r</locus>
                           <desc>: An antiphon dedicated to St George (cp. </desc>
                           <locus target="#98rc">98rc</locus>).<quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#106r">106r</locus>: ጊዮርጊስ፡ ኃያል፡ መስተጋድል፡ አበሰ፡
                              ዘይዘሪ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in hand b, apparently as a writing exercise.
                              Below the note there is a pen trial signed by Walda Gabra Nazrawi.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Cues for rubricators: <locus target="#58rv">58rv</locus>, 59rv, 69v, 70rv, 71v, 72rv, 73r, 74rv, 75r, 76rv, 81v,
                           82r, 83rv, 84rv, 85rv, 86rv, 88v, 101v, 102r, 104r.
 - Directives for
                           the ministers are written in the upper margin, in a secondary hand:
                              <locus target="#59vb">59vb</locus>c, 70va. 
 - Tamallas-sign, in
                           the shape of a cross, indicating the place where the omissions, written
                           in the upper margin in the main hand, belong: <locus target="#2vb">2vb</locus> l.8, 14ra l.10, 61rc l.7, 61vb l.16, 62va l.8, 62va l.14,
                           66ra l.15, 66va l.16, 70rb l.14, 70va l.1, 72va l.1, 75rb l.4, 76vc l.2,
                           78va l.8, 80vb <locus target="#18">18</locus>, 81vc l.9.
 -
                           Tamallas-sign, in the shape of a cross, indicating the place where the
                           omissions, written interlineally in the main hand, belong: <locus target="#80vc">80vc</locus> l.20, 80vc l.21, 82va l.15, 86ra
                           l.20.
 - Omitted passages written in the margins: <locus target="#69vc">69vc</locus>, 79rc, 91rc, 93rb, 93vb, 95rc, 96rab,
                           97rb, 97v, 99vb, 100rb. 
 - Pen trial: <locus target="#92r">92r</locus>, 99r, 106r.
 - Scribbles: <locus target="#102v">102v</locus>, 103r, 105v, 106r.</item>
                     </list>
